{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879127122,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa5004f0012dSAouZu3v2VwU","messageID":"msg_d7aa4f1a1001Tat6Q1kDHr8fPZ","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879129087,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa502ca001jB2pDtsWeMt8M7","messageID":"msg_d7aa4f1a1001Tat6Q1kDHr8fPZ","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3162a2a898fe46d1a2c03638","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-036/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-036: Dify 插件集成\n2: \n3: **Module:** integrations  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T001** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **T002** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` with entry point `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n14: - [ ] **T003** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` with required Dify plugin metadata (version 0.0.2, type plugin, author volcano-sh, name agentcube, labels, icons, resources)\n15: - [ ] **T004** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` with `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n16: - [ ] **T005** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` file\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Phase 2: Plugin Icons\n21: \n22: - [ ] **T010** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/icon.png` (plugin icon light)\n23: - [ ] **T011** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/icon-dark.png` (plugin icon dark)\n24: \n25: ---\n26: \n27: ## Phase 3: Tool Provider Descriptor\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T020** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.yaml` with identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n30: - [ ] **T021** Verify provider descriptor contains `identity`, `tools`, and `extra.python.source`\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## Phase 4: Tool Provider Implementation\n35: \n36: - [ ] **T030** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/provider/agentcube.py` with `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterProvider` class extending `ToolProvider`\n37: - [ ] **T031** Implement `_validate_credentials(self, credentials: dict[str, Any]) -> None` method\n38: - [ ] **T032** Implement error handling that raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n39: \n40: ---\n41: \n42: ## Phase 5: Tool Descriptor\n43: \n44: - [ ] **T040** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml` with complete parameter schema\n45: - [ ] **T041** Verify tool schema includes all parameters: router_url, workload_manager_url, language, code, command, session_id, session_reuse, code_interpreter_id\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## Phase 6: Tool Implementation\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T050** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.py` with `AgentcubeCodeInterpreterTool` class\n52: - [ ] **T051** Implement `_invoke` method that yields JSON messages via `create_json_message`\n53: - [ ] **T052** Implement `execute` method delegating to `CodeInterpreterClient` from agentcube SDK\n54: - [ ] **T053** Handle SDK exceptions including `CommandExecutionError`\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## Phase 7: Plugin Documentation\n59: \n60: - [ ] **T060** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/README.md` with plugin documentation\n61: - [ ] **T061** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md` with usage guide\n62: - [ ] **T062** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md` with privacy policy\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: ## Phase 8: PCAP Analyzer Application\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T070** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory structure\n69: - [ ] **T071** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` FastAPI application\n70: - [ ] **T072** Implement startup validation for `OPENAI_API_KEY` (fail if missing)\n71: - [ ] **T073** Implement `/analyze` endpoint accepting `pcap_file` upload or `pcap_path` parameter\n72: - [ ] **T074** Configure default values: OPENAI_API_BASE, OPENAI_MODEL, CODEINTERPRETER_NAME, SANDBOX_NAMESPACE, SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\n73: - [ ] **T075** Implement agent orchestration with PLANNER and REPORTER agents\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Phase 9: PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n78: \n79: - [ ] **T080** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` with FastAPI, LangChain, and agentcube-sdk dependencies\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## Phase 10: PCAP Analyzer Sandbox Integration\n84: \n85: - [ ] **T090** Implement `SandboxRunner` class with upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n86: - [ ] **T091** Integrate SandboxRunner with PCAP analysis workflow\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Phase 11: PCAP Analyzer Container\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T100** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` with uv base image, Python 3.12, port 8000 exposure\n93: - [ ] **T101** Configure Dockerfile to vendor agentcube SDK\n94: - [ ] **T102** Verify `docker build -f example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile -t pcap-analyzer:test .` succeeds\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ## Phase 12: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n99: \n100: - [ ] **T110** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` with Deployment manifest\n101: - [ ] **T111** Configure resource requests (cpu: 200m, memory: 100Mi) and limits (cpu: 1, memory: 1Gi)\n102: - [ ] **T112** Wire environment variables and secrets from pcap-analyzer-secrets\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## Phase 13: PCAP Analyzer Documentation\n107: \n108: - [ ] **T120** Create `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` with analyzer documentation\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## Phase 14: Integration Verification\n113: \n114: - [ ] **T130** Verify Dify plugin structure matches requirements (AR-036-001)\n115: - [ ] **T131** Verify manifest.yaml contains all required fields (AR-036-002)\n116: - [ ] **T132** Verify tool provider and tool descriptors are correctly wired (AR-036-003, AR-036-004)\n117: - [ ] **T133** Verify PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup (AR-036-008-B)\n118: - [ ] **T134** Verify PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint functionality (AR-036-008-C, AR-036-008-D)\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Dependencies\n123: \n124: ```\n125: Phase 1 (T001-T005) → Phase 2 (T010-T011) → Phase 3-7 (T020-T062)\n126: Phase 8-10 (T070-T091) can parallel after Phase 1\n127: Phase 11 (T100-T102) depends on Phase 8-10\n128: Phase 12 (T110-T112) depends on Phase 11\n129: Phase 13 (T120) depends on Phase 8\n130: Phase 14 (T130-T134) depends on Phases 1-13\n131: ```\n132: \n133: **Parallel:** Phases 8-10 (PCAP Analyzer core) can be done in parallel with Phases 3-7 (Dify plugin components)\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## Acceptance Criteria\n138: \n139: - [ ] AC001: Plugin package contains all required files (main.py, manifest.yaml, provider files, tool files, requirements.txt)\n140: - [ ] AC002: Plugin entry point executes `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n141: - [ ] AC003: manifest.yaml contains all required Dify plugin metadata fields\n142: - [ ] AC004: Provider descriptor (`provider/agentcube.yaml`) contains identity, tools list, and Python source reference\n143: - [ ] AC005: Tool descriptor (`tools/agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml`) contains complete parameter schema\n144: - [ ] AC006: Provider implementation raises `ToolProviderCredentialValidationError` on invalid credentials\n145: - [ ] AC007: Tool implementation delegates to `CodeInterpreterClient` and returns JSON messages\n146: - [ ] AC008: requirements.txt pins `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n147: - [ ] AC009: PCAP analyzer validates API key at startup and fails if missing\n148: - [ ] AC010: PCAP analyzer `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload or path parameter\n149: - [ ] AC011: PCAP analyzer uses default configuration values when env vars are not set\n150: - [ ] AC012: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, upload_bytes, run, and stop methods\n151: - [ ] AC013: Dockerfile uses uv base image, exposes port 8000, runs pcap_analyzer.py\n152: - [ ] AC014: Kubernetes deployment wires secrets and environment variables correctly\n153: - [ ] AC015: SDK exceptions (CommandExecutionError) are properly handled\n154: \n155: ---\n156: \n157: ## Verification Commands\n158: \n159: ```bash\n160: # Plugin structure verification\n161: ls -la integrations/dify-plugin/\n162: ls -la integrations/dify-plugin/provider/\n163: ls -la integrations/dify-plugin/tools/\n164: \n165: # PCAP analyzer build\n166: docker build -f example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile -t pcap-analyzer:test .\n167: \n168: # PCAP analyzer run\n169: docker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n170:   -e OPENAI_API_KEY=$OPENAI_API_KEY \\\n171:   -e ROUTER_URL=http://router:8080 \\\n172:   -e WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workload-manager:8080 \\\n173:   pcap-analyzer:test\n174: \n175: # Test analyze endpoint (with file)\n176: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n177:   -F \"pcap_file=@capture.pcap\"\n178: \n179: # Test analyze endpoint (with path)\n180: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n181:   -F \"pcap_path=/data/capture.pcap\"\n182: ```\n\n(End of file - total 182 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-036: Dify 插件集成\n\n**Module:** integrations  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Design Stage:** ST-3 completed\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Dify Plugin Package Structure\n\n- [ ] **T001** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/` directory structure\n- [ ] **T002** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/main.py` with entry point `Plugin(DifyPluginEnv(MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=120)).run()`\n- [ ] **T003** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/manifest.yaml` with required Dify plugin metadata (version 0.0.2, type plugin, author volcano-sh, name agentcube, labels, icons, resources)\n- [ ] **T004** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/requirements.txt` with `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0` and `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n- [ ] **T005** Create `integrations/dify-plugin/.difyignore` file\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Plugin Icons","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspa