{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879243078,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa69e49001EJkhw2d674ygBD","messageID":"msg_d7aa6957a001q3mw7GUrAqNikZ","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d4af1cede9614b0cbb22a371","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Dify Plugin\n\nA Dify plugin for integrating AgentCube Code Interpreter into your Dify workflows.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe AgentCube plugin allows Dify users to execute Python and other code in isolated AgentCube sandboxes directly from their AI agents and workflows.\n\n## Features\n\n- Execute Python code in isolated sandboxes\n- Support for session reuse for stateful workflows\n- File upload and download capabilities\n- Package installation support\n- Shell command execution\n- Multiple language support (Python, JavaScript, TypeScript)\n\n## Installation\n\n1. Build the plugin:\n   ```bash\n   cd integrations/dify-plugin\n   pip install -r requirements.txt\n   ```\n\n2. Package the plugin:\n   ```bash\n   zip -r agentcube.zip . -x \".git/*\"\n   ```\n\n3. Install in Dify:\n   - Go to Settings > Plugin Marketplace\n   - Click \"Install Plugin\"\n   - Upload the `agentcube.zip` file\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Required Credentials\n\n- **router_url**: The URL of the AgentCube Router service\n- **workload_manager_url**: The URL of the AgentCube Workload Manager service\n\n### Optional Parameters\n\n- **language**: Programming language (default: \"python\")\n- **session_reuse**: Reuse sessions for stateful workflows\n- **code_interpreter_id**: Specific interpreter instance ID\n\n## Usage\n\n### In Dify Agent\n\n1. Create a new Agent or Workflow\n2. Add the \"AgentCube Code Interpreter\" tool\n3. Configure the router_url and workload_manager_url\n4. Use the tool in your prompts\n\nExample prompt:\n```\nUse the AgentCube Code Interpreter to execute the following Python code:\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\ndata = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]\ndf = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=['numbers'])\nprint(df.describe())\n```\n```\n\n### Tool Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| router_url | string | Yes | AgentCube Router URL |\n| workload_manager_url | string | Yes | Workload Manager URL |\n| language | select | No | Programming language |\n| code | string | No* | Code to execute |\n| command | string | No* | Shell command |\n| session_id | string | No | Reuse existing session |\n| session_reuse | boolean | No | Enable session reuse |\n\n*Either `code` or `command` must be provided.\n\n## Development\n\n### Project Structure\n\n```\ndify-plugin/\n├── main.py                  # Plugin entry point\n├── manifest.yaml           # Plugin metadata\n├── requirements.txt        # Python dependencies\n├── provider/\n│   ├── agentcube.yaml      # Provider descriptor\n│   └── agentcube.py        # Provider implementation\n├── tools/\n│   ├── agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml  # Tool schema\n│   └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py   # Tool implementation\n└── ...\n```\n\n### Running Tests\n\n```bash\npip install pytest pytest-mock\npytest tests/\n```\n\n## License\n\nApache 2.0","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/integrations/dify-plugin/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [99:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [102:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignabl