{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879260516,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa6cd630013bqcTKZwF43ov8","messageID":"msg_d7aa6c570001fkfks68q4Uax4K","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_b3fa15b529cc481e8d52e3df","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Dify Plugin Usage Guide\n\n## Getting Started\n\nThis guide walks you through setting up and using the AgentCube Code Interpreter plugin in Dify.\n\n### Prerequisites\n\n- A Dify installation (self-hosted or cloud)\n- Access to AgentCube services (Router and Workload Manager)\n- Valid API credentials for AgentCube\n\n### Step 1: Install the Plugin\n\n1. Navigate to your Dify instance\n2. Go to **Settings** > **Plugin Marketplace**\n3. Click **Install Plugin**\n4. Upload the `agentcube.zip` package\n\n### Step 2: Configure Credentials\n\nAfter installation, configure the tool provider:\n\n1. Find \"AgentCube Code Interpreter\" in your tool list\n2. Click **Configure**\n3. Enter the required credentials:\n\n   - **Router URL**: `http://<router-host>:8080` (or your Router service address)\n   - **Workload Manager URL**: `http://<workload-manager-host>:8080` (or your Workload Manager address)\n\n4. Click **Save**\n\n### Step 3: Use in Agent\n\nTo use the Code Interpreter in a Dify Agent:\n\n1. Create a new Agent or edit an existing one\n2. Click **Add Tool**\n3. Select **AgentCube Code Interpreter**\n4. Write your prompt with code to execute\n\nExample:\n```\nUse the AgentCube Code Interpreter to calculate the first 20 Fibonacci numbers and return the sum.\n```\n\n### Step 4: Use in Workflow\n\nTo use in a Workflow:\n\n1. Create a new Workflow\n2. Add an **Agent** node\n3. Configure the agent with the Code Interpreter tool\n4. Connect to your LLM node\n\n## Advanced Usage\n\n### Session Reuse\n\nFor workflows requiring stateful execution:\n\n1. Enable **Session Reuse** in tool parameters\n2. Use the same `session_id` across multiple tool calls\n\nExample workflow:\n```\nNode 1: Initialize data\n  - Code: data = []\n  - session_reuse: true\n\nNode 2: Append data\n  - Code: data.append(42)\n  - session_id: <use session from Node 1>\n  - session_reuse: true\n\nNode 3: Final analysis\n  - Code: print(sum(data))\n  - session_id: <use session from Node 2>\n```\n\n### File Operations\n\nUpload files to the sandbox:\n\n```python\n# Use the tool with upload capabilities\n# Files can be uploaded via the CodeInterpreterClient\n```\n\n### Shell Commands\n\nExecute shell commands directly:\n\n```bash\n# Set command parameter instead of code\ncommand: \"ls -la /tmp\"\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Connection Errors\n\n- Verify Router and Workload Manager URLs are accessible\n- Check firewall rules allow traffic on required ports\n\n### Timeout Errors\n\n- Increase `MAX_REQUEST_TIMEOUT` in main.py for long-running code\n- Break large computations into smaller chunks\n\n### Session Errors\n\n- If sessions expire unexpectedly, implement session renewal logic\n- Use session_reuse carefully to avoid stale state\n\n## Best Practices\n\n1. **Always set timeouts** for long-running computations\n2. **Use session reuse** only when state is required\n3. **Handle exceptions** in your prompts to gracefully manage failures\n4. **Test locally** before deploying to production\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- Keep your Router and Workload Manager URLs secure\n- Implement proper authentication for production use\n- Restrict network access to AgentCube services\n\n## API Reference\n\n### Tool Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| router_url | string | yes | - | AgentCube Router URL |\n| workload_manager_url | string | yes | - | Workload Manager URL |\n| language | string | no | python | Programming language |\n| code | string | no* | - | Code to execute |\n| command | string | no* | - | Shell command |\n| session_id | string | no | - | Existing session ID |\n| session_reuse | boolean | no | false | Reuse session |\n| code_interpreter_id | string | no | - | Interpreter instance ID |\n\n*Either `code` or `command` must be provided.\n\n### Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"session_id\": \"session-123\",\n  \"stdout\": \"Result output\",\n  \"stderr\": \"\",\n  \"exit_code\": 0\n}\n```\n\n### Error Response\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"error\": \"CommandExecutionError\",\n  \"message\": \"Error description\",\n  \"exit_code\": 1,\n  \"stderr\": \"Error output\"\n}\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/integrations/dify-plugin/GUIDE.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [99:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [102:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [109:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [137:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [139:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [147:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable t