{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879269966,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa71451001dzHKWBRaoOXXPp","messageID":"msg_d7aa7099b001gyq7LhItH9690F","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1b2aff3f472042c6a699261b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AgentCube Dify Plugin Privacy Policy\n\n## Data Collection\n\nThe AgentCube Dify plugin processes code and data as follows:\n\n### Data Processing\n\n- **Code Execution**: Code submitted through the plugin is executed in isolated AgentCube sandboxes\n- **Session Data**: Session IDs are generated and stored to enable stateful workflows\n- **Credentials**: Router and Workload Manager URLs are stored securely within Dify's credential system\n\n### Data Storage\n\n- **No Persistent Storage**: The plugin does not store any data persistently\n- **Temporary Sessions**: Session data exists only during active execution\n- **No External Data Transfer**: Code and results are processed only between Dify and AgentCube services\n\n## Security\n\n### Credential Handling\n\n- Credentials are stored using Dify's secure credential storage\n- Credentials are never logged or exposed in outputs\n- Credentials are transmitted only to configured AgentCube services\n\n### Network Security\n\n- All communication uses HTTPS when configured\n- Internal network communication uses authenticated channels\n- No third-party services receive your data\n\n## User Responsibilities\n\n### Input Validation\n\nUsers should:\n- Validate code before execution\n- Avoid submitting sensitive data (keys, passwords) in code\n- Review code for security vulnerabilities\n\n### Credential Management\n\n- Use least-privilege credentials when possible\n- Rotate credentials periodically\n- Restrict network access to AgentCube services\n\n## Compliance\n\nThis plugin is designed to comply with:\n- Data processing agreements with AgentCube services\n- Standard security best practices for credential handling\n- Isolated execution environment for code processing\n\n## Updates\n\nThis privacy policy may be updated periodically. Users will be notified of any material changes.\n\n## Contact\n\nFor privacy concerns, contact:\n- Email: security@volcano.sh\n- GitHub: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/integrations/dify-plugin/PRIVACY.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [99:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"router_url\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [102:28] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"__init__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [109:59] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"session_id\" of type \"str\" in function \"delete_session\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [137:30] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [139:31] Cannot access attribute \"get\" for class \"str\"\n  Attribute \"get\" is unknown\nERROR [147:16] Type \"str\" is not assignable to return type \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n  \"str\" is not assignable to \"Dict[Unknown, Unknown]\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/integrations/dify-plugin/main.py\">\nERROR [1:6] Import \"dify