{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879347982,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa85f0c0017ochh2LNP59Gqt","messageID":"msg_d7aa8570e0012HGu23VBzob9ha","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879368354,"sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa860970015SeL4TT99kHZUZ","messageID":"msg_d7aa8570e0012HGu23VBzob9ha","sessionID":"ses_2855b5dd5ffeXhI1DCutoRh24A","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_668d50e835254ce1a0f82e83","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# PCAP Analyzer\n\nNetwork traffic analysis service using AgentCube Code Interpreter and LLM orchestration.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe PCAP Analyzer is a FastAPI application that provides an API for analyzing network capture (PCAP) files using AI-powered agents. It leverages AgentCube's Code Interpreter to execute Python code for network traffic analysis.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌──────────────────┐\n│   Client    │────▶│  FastAPI    │────▶│  LLM Orchestrator│\n└─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     └──────────────────┘\n                                                │\n                   ┌────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┐\n                   │                            │                            │\n                   ▼                            ▼                            ▼\n            ┌─────────────┐             ┌─────────────┐            ┌─────────────┐\n            │  Planner    │             │   ReAct     │            │  Reporter  │\n            │   Agent     │             │    Agent    │            │   Agent    │\n            └─────────────┘             └─────────────┘            └─────────────┘\n                   │                            │                            │\n                   └────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────┘\n                                                │\n                                     ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n                                     │ AgentCube Sandbox   │\n                                     │ (Code Interpreter)  │\n                                     └─────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- **LLM-Powered Analysis**: Uses large language models to generate analysis scripts\n- **ReAct Agent**: Implements Reasoning + Acting pattern for interactive analysis\n- **Sandbox Execution**: Runs Python code securely in AgentCube sandboxes\n- **REST API**: Simple HTTP API for submitting PCAP files and getting analysis results\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Python 3.12+\n- OpenAI-compatible API key\n- Access to AgentCube services (Router and Workload Manager)\n\n## Installation\n\n### Local Development\n\n```bash\n# Clone the repository\ncd example/pcap-analyzer\n\n# Create virtual environment\npython -m venv .venv\nsource .venv/bin/activate\n\n# Install dependencies\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Set environment variables\nexport OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key\nexport ROUTER_URL=http://localhost:8080\nexport WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://localhost:8080\n\n# Run the server\npython pcap_analyzer.py\n```\n\n### Docker\n\n```bash\n# Build the image\ndocker build -t pcap-analyzer:latest .\n\n# Run the container\ndocker run -p 8000:8000 \\\n  -e OPENAI_API_KEY=your-api-key \\\n  -e ROUTER_URL=http://router:8080 \\\n  -e WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL=http://workload-manager:8080 \\\n  pcap-analyzer:latest\n```\n\n### Kubernetes\n\n```bash\n# Update the secret with your API key\nkubectl create secret generic pcap-analyzer-secrets \\\n  --from-literal=openai-api-key=your-api-key\n\n# Apply the deployment\nkubectl apply -f deployment.yaml\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\nThe following environment variables can be configured:\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | (required) | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n| `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | API endpoint |\n| `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | Model name |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Router URL |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | (required) | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n| `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | Code interpreter name |\n| `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | Sandbox warmup duration |\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### POST /analyze\n\nAnalyze a PCAP file.\n\n**Request:**\n\n```bash\n# With file upload\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n  -F \"pcap_file=@capture.pcap\" \\\n  -F \"question=What are the top talkers in this network?\"\n\n# With file path\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8000/analyze \\\n  -F \"pcap_path=/data/capture.pcap\" \\\n  -F \"question=List all HTTP requests\"\n```\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"script\": \"from scapy.all import *\\n...\",\n  \"results\": \"10.0.0.1: 1234 packets\\n10.0.0.2: 567 packets\",\n  \"report\": \"## Analysis Report\\n\\n...\"\n}\n```\n\n### GET /health\n\nHealth check endpoint.\n\n**Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"healthy\"\n}\n```\n\n## Components\n\n### SandboxRunner\n\nManages the AgentCube sandbox session, including:\n- Starting and stopping sessions\n- Uploading files\n- Executing commands\n\n### Planner Agent\n\nGenerates Python scripts for PCAP analysis based on the user's question.\n\n### ReAct Agent\n\nImplements the Reasoning + Acting pattern for iterative analysis.\n\n### Reporter Agent\n\nGenerates human-readable reports from analysis results.\n\n## Example Questions\n\n- \"What are the top 10 source IP addresses by packet count?\"\n- \"List all HTTP requests and their response codes\"\n- \"What protocols are used in this capture?\"\n- \"Show DNS queries and their responses\"\n- \"Find all TCP connections\"\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### OPENAI_API_KEY not set\n\n```\nERROR: OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable is not set\n```\n\nSet the environment variable before starting the service.\n\n### Connection refused to Router/Workload Manager\n\nEnsure AgentCube services are running and accessible from the analyzer.\n\n### Analysis timeout\n\nIncrease the timeout or simplify the analysis question.\n\n## License\n\nApache 2.0","filePath":"/home/dsj/bench